To compress the height of the hamburger menu icon (typically composed of three horizontal bars), you can modify the CSS that defines the height and spacing of the bars. This usually involves adjusting the `height`, `margin`, and `padding` of the bars that form the hamburger icon.

Here's an example of how you can compress the height of the bars:

### HTML (for reference):
```html
<div class="hamburger">
  <span></span>
  <span></span>
  <span></span>
</div>
```

### CSS:
```css
.hamburger {
  display: inline-block;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.hamburger span {
  display: block;
  width: 35px;  /* Width of the bars */
  height: 3px;  /* Height of the bars */
  background-color: #333;  /* Color of the bars */
  margin: 4px 0;  /* Space between bars */
  transition: 0.4s;
}

/* To compress the height, adjust the height and margin values */
```

### Key Modifications:
- **Height of each bar (`height`)**: Decrease this value to make the bars thinner.
- **Space between bars (`margin`)**: Decrease this value to reduce the spacing between the bars.

For example, if you want the hamburger menu to be more compressed:
```css
.hamburger span {
  width: 35px;
  height: 2px;  /* Thinner bars */
  margin: 2px 0;  /* Less space between bars */
  background-color: #333;
  transition: 0.4s;
}
```

This will make the hamburger menu appear more compressed vertically, as the bars will be thinner and the space between them will be reduced. You can adjust these values further depending on how compressed you want the hamburger icon to be.

